chunk_content: The “all children” N column indicates that any child or adolescent may be counted if they receive the service and meet the other requirements D for active status (i.e., a current case plan and at least quarterly monitoring). The “caregiver and child” column indicates I C the activity completed by the caregiver may be counted toward both the child and caregiver as it provides direct benefit E to the child. Services with a mark in both one of the child columns and the caregiver columns indicate the activity may be S provided to and directly benefit a child and/or a caregiver; if a caregiver receives such a service, it may only be counted towards the caregiver and not both the caregiver and the child (in contrast to activities checked in the “caregiver and child column”). This list while comprehensive is not exhaustive.
